%20in%20early%202021%20and%20defied%20warnings%20of%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-died-of-sudden-death-syndrome-his-mother-told-5076885%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavalny's%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20been%20confirmed%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Cofficial%20message%E2%80%9D%20to%20his%20mother%2C%20said%20Kira%20Yarmysh%2C%20his%20spokesperson%2C%20on%20the%20X%20social%20media%20platform%20and%20in%20a%20video%20statement%20on%20Saturday.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20the%20opposition%20activist%20follows%20a%20fatal%20plane%20crash%20that%20killed%20Wagner%20mercenary%20group%20leader%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-to-yevgeny-prigozhin-heres-a-list-of-putin-critics-who-died-mysteriously-5074087%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYevgeny%20Prigozhin%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20Prigozhin%2C%20who%20became%20a%20hero%20to%20Russian%20nationalists%20for%20his%20part%20in%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20was%20reported%20killed%20in%20August%2C%20exactly%20two%20months%20after%20leading%20a%20mutiny%20against%20the%20Defense%20Ministry's%20leadership%20that%20spiraled%20into%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20Putin's%20nearly%20quarter-century%20rule.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20incidents%20serve%20to%20remove%20figures%20who%20publicly%20opposed%20Putin%2C%20though%20from%20very%20different%20perspectives.%20That%20alone%20sends%20a%20powerful%20message%20to%20Russians%20and%20to%20the%20world%20as%20the%20second%20anniversary%20nears%20of%20Putin's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20that%20triggered%20a%20wave%20of%20sanctions%20and%20prompted%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20to%20supply%20weaponry%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20death%20was%20announced%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20official%20campaigning%20for%20the%20March%2017%20presidential%20election%20in%20which%20Putin%20is%20seeking%20a%20fifth%20term.%20Government%20leaders%20quickly%20accused%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20some%20directly%20blamed%20Putin%2C%20the%20former%20KGB%20officer%20who's%20on%20course%20to%20equal%20Soviet%20tyrant%20Josef%20Stalin's%20record%20term%20as%20ruler%20in%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20authorities%20have%20yet%20to%20disclose%20a%20cause%20of%20death%2C%20saying%20Navalny%20felt%20unwell%20after%20a%20walk%20and%20lost%20consciousness.%20Just%20a%20day%20earlier%2C%20he'd%20appeared%20on%20video%20from%20prison%20at%20a%20court%20hearing%2C%20joking%20cheerfully%20with%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20was%20so%20hostile%20to%20Navalny%20that%20he%20refused%20to%20use%20his%20name%20when%20reporters%20asked%20questions%20about%20the%20activist%2C%20a%20trend%20followed%20by%20Kremlin%20spokesperson%20Dmitry%20Peskov.%20Russian%20state%20television%2C%20which%20for%20years%20had%20banned%20any%20mention%20of%20Navalny%2C%20briefly%20reported%20his%20demise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20relations%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20West%20already%20largely%20severed%20over%20Putin's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%20on%20Feb.%2024%2C%202022%2C%20it's%20unclear%20if%20US%20and%20European%20condemnation%20of%20Navalny's%20death%20will%20turn%20into%20more%20concrete%20penalties%20against%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFriends%20and%20allies%20of%20Navalny%20had%20worried%20constantly%20for%20his%20safety%20in%20prison%20as%20the%20Kremlin%20engaged%20in%20the%20biggest%20crackdown%20on%20dissent%20in%20decades%20to%20crush%20opposition%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20concern%20intensified%20when%20Navalny%2C%2047%2C%20was%20transferred%20to%20a%20remote%20Arctic%20prison%20colony%2C%20IK-3%2C%20in%20late%20December%20from%20a%20jail%20outside%20Moscow.%20In%20his%20last%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20on%20Feb.%2014%2C%20he%20reported%20that%20he'd%20been%20sentenced%20to%2015%20days%20in%20a%20punishment%20cell%20for%20the%20fourth%20time%20since%20he'd%20arrived%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe'd%20been%20advocating%20from%20prison%20on%20social%20media%20for%20a%20nationwide%20protest%20during%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20encouraging%20people%20to%20arrive%20at%20polling%20stations%20at%20exactly%20midday%20to%20vote%20against%20Putin.%20Navalny%20had%20also%20condemned%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20death%20is%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20string%20of%20incidents%20involving%20leading%20critics%20of%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdead-jailed-or-exiled-putins-best-known-critics-and-where-they-are-now-5070715%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20deputy%20prime%20minister%2C%20was%20assassinated%20in%20Moscow%20within%20sight%20of%20the%20Kremlin%20walls%20in%20February%202015.%20Campaigning%20journalist%20Anna%20Politkovskaya%20was%20shot%20dead%20in%20the%20lift%20of%20her%20Moscow%20apartment%20building%20on%20Putin's%20birthday%20in%20October%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVladimir%20Kara-Murza%2C%20another%20prominent%20opposition%20figure%20sentenced%20to%2025%20years%20for%20treason%20in%20April%20after%20he%20condemned%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20has%20accused%20the%20Russian%20authorities%20of%20twice%20poisoning%20him%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20early%20years%20at%20least%2C%20Navalny%20courted%20controversy%20by%20reaching%20out%20to%20nationalist%20elements%20who%20were%20hostile%20to%20the%20Kremlin%20as%20well%20as%20to%20foreigners%20and%20minorities.%20Navalny%20justified%20the%20ties%20by%20arguing%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20broad%20coalition%20against%20Putin%2C%20but%20many%20liberal%20activists%20remained%20suspicious%20of%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFearless%20and%20Internet-savvy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-putin-critic-dies-in-prison-why-was-russian-leader-in-jail-5070104%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavalny%3C%2Fa%3E%20gained%20a%20huge%20online%20following%20in%20Russia%20with%20investigations%20exposing%20corruption%20at%20state%20companies%20and%20among%20top%20officials%2C%20using%20social%20media%20posts%20to%20bypass%20the%20blackout%20on%20state%20television.%20In%20January%202021%2C%20he%20caused%20a%20storm%20with%20a%20video%20exposing%20a%20lavish%20%241.3%20billion%20Black%20Sea%20palace%20that%20he%20said%20was%20built%20for%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20video%2C%20which%20has%20been%20viewed%20more%20than%20129%20million%20times%20on%20YouTube%2C%20was%20released%20after%20Navalny%20was%20detained%20when%20he%20returned%20to%20Russia%20from%20Germany%2C%20where%20he'd%20been%20treated%20for%20a%20nerve-agent%20poisoning%20in%20Siberia%20in%202020%20that%20he%20and%20the%20West%20blamed%20on%20the%20Kremlin.%20Russia%20denied%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20year%2C%20Russia%20outlawed%20Navalny's%20nationwide%20network%20of%20campaign%20groups%20as%20%26quot%3Bextremist%2C%26quot%3B%20forcing%20activists%20to%20disband%20and%20many%20to%20flee%20abroad.%20Navalny%20himself%20was%20suffering%20from%20worsening%20health%20in%20prison%20and%20looked%20gaunt%20at%20court%20hearings%20after%20spending%2024%20days%20on%20hunger%20strike%20to%20demand%20better%20medical%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20the%20opposition%20leader%20and%20his%20movement%2C%20made%20up%20of%20mostly%20young%20professionals%2C%20contrasted%20starkly%20with%20the%20early%20optimism%20of%20the%20massive%20protests%20in%202011-2012%20against%20Putin's%20return%20to%20the%20presidency%20in%20place%20of%20Dmitry%20Medvedev.%20The%20Kremlin%20crackdown%20that%20had%20followed%20failed%20to%20dim%20their%20determination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Navalny%20was%20unexpectedly%20allowed%20to%20contest%20Moscow%20mayoral%20elections%20in%20September%202013%2C%20following%20widespread%20protests%20in%20support%20of%20his%20release%20from%20detention%2C%20he%20came%20within%20a%20whisker%20of%20forcing%20a%20run-off%20against%20Sergei%20Sobyanin%2C%20the%20incumbent%20Putin%20ally.%20He%20got%2027%25%20against%2051%25%20for%20Sobyanin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20last%20time%20Navalny%20was%20permitted%20to%20run.%20When%20he%20mounted%20a%20campaign%20to%20challenge%20Putin%20in%20the%202018%20presidential%20election%2C%20officials%20barred%20him%20from%20the%20ballot%20because%20of%20a%20fraud%20conviction%20that%20Navalny%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20had%20criticized%20as%20politically%20motivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNavalny%20was%20essentially%20killed%20when%20he%20was%20arrested%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Thad%20Troy%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20Crumpton%20Global%20and%20a%20former%20CIA%20officer%20in%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20inevitable%20next%20step%20for%20Putin%20to%20strengthen%20his%20hold%20over%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20prison%2C%20Navalny%20continued%20his%20defiance%20of%20Putin.%20He%20also%20disclosed%20that%20he'd%20developed%20a%20belief%20in%20God%20after%20years%20of%20atheism%2C%20surprising%20many%20of%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20country%20is%20built%20on%20injustice.%20But%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20want%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20a%20court%20during%20a%20failed%202021%20appeal%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20sooner%20or%20later%20they'll%20get%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708224000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Ffg4c665g_alexey-navalny-vladimir-putin_625x300_18_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%