-parent-sue-mental-health-teens-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-sue-meta-allege-facebook-instagram-harm-youth-mental-health-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20on%20our%20mental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIronically%2C%20we%20are%20more%20connected%20and%20plugged%20in%20than%20ever%20before%20through%20advances%20in%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Nicole%20Siegfried%2C%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20chief%20clinical%20officer%20at%20Lightfully%20Behavior%20Health%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20what%20we%20have%20learned%20is%20that%20being%20connected%20through%20technology%20does%20not%20necessarily%20promote%20feelings%20of%20connection.%20In%20fact%2C%20most%20research%20demonstrates%20that%20loneliness%20increases%20with%20increased%20use%20of%20technology%2C%20especially%20social%20media%20sites.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20phenomenon%20may%20be%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20true%20connection%20is%20achieved%20through%20feelings%20of%20being%20known%2C%20understood%2C%20accepted%2C%20and%20safe%20with%20another%20being.%20The%20ways%20in%20which%20we%20currently%20utilize%20technology%20block%20us%20from%20this%20experience%20of%20true%20connection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20isn't%20all%20bad%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20and%20it%20does%20have%20the%20power%20to%20connect%20us.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-radically-reshape-job-market-global-economy-employee-labor-innovation-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETech%20innovations%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20made%20communication%20quicker%20and%20easier%20regardless%20of%20location%2C%20enabled%20accessible%20interactions%20for%20people%20with%20limited%20social%20contact%2C%20and%20extended%20social%20support%20networks%20from%20those%20in%20our