20Kira%20Yarmysh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20obvious%20that%20the%20killers%20want%20to%20cover%20their%20tracks%20and%20are%20therefore%20not%20handing%20over%20Alexei's%20body%2C%20hiding%20it%20even%20from%20his%20mother%2C%26quot%3B%20Navalny's%20team%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20police%20on%20Saturday%20moved%20swiftly%20to%20break%20up%20small%20protests%20and%20memorials%20in%20honour%20of%20the%20dead%20Kremlin%20critic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20arrested%20more%20than%20340%20people%20in%2030%20cities%2C%20the%20OVD-Info%20rights%20group%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20capital%20Moscow%2C%20AFP%20reporters%20saw%20two%20people%20being%20detained%20at%20a%20makeshift%20tribute%20in%20central%20Moscow%2C%20while%20hundreds%20of%20tearful%20mourners%20laid%20flowers%20in%20the%20snow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlexei%20Navalny's%20death%20is%20the%20worst%20thing%20that%20could%20happen%20to%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20note%20left%20among%20the%20flowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPutin%20'responsible'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20initially%20pushing%20back%20at%20accusations%20they%20were%20to%20blame%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20made%20no%20mention%20of%20his%20death%20on%20Saturday%2C%20despite%20an%20angry%20chorus%20of%20condemnation%20from%20Western%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG7%20foreign%20ministers%20meeting%20in%20Munich%20held%20a%20minute's%20silence%20for%20the%20leader%20on%20Saturday%2C%20while%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20pointed%20the%20blame%20at%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMake%20no%20mistake%2C%20Putin%20is%20responsible%20for%20Navalny's%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%20hours%20after%20news%20of%20her%20husband's%20death%2C%20Yulia%20Navalnaya%20said%20Putin%20and%20his%20entourage%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bpunished%20for%20everything%20they%20have%20done%20to%20our%20country%2C%20to%20my%20family%20and%20to%20my%20husband%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20called%20on%20the%20international%20community%20to%20%26quot%3Bunite%20and%20defeat%20this%20evil%2C%20terrifying%20regime%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20winner%20Dmitry%20Muratov%20said%20Navalny's%20death%20was%20%26quot%3Bmurder%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Btortured%20and%20tormented%26quot%3B%20for%20all%20of%20the%20three%20years%20he%20spent%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETributes%20continued%20to%20pour%20in%20on%20Saturday%2C%20as%20supporters%20staged%20anti-Putin%20protests%20and%20set%20up%20memorials%20to%20Navalny%20at%20Russian%20diplomatic%20missions%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Russia%2C%20police%20detained%20hundreds%20of%20people%20who%20had%20laid%20flowers%20at%20monuments%20to%20the%20victims%20of%20political%20repression%2C%20rights%20groups%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20posted%20by%20the%20independent%20Sota%20outlet%20from%20the%20capital%20Moscow%2C%20a%20woman%20could%20be%20heard%20screaming%20as%20a%20crowd%20of%20police%20officers%20forcefully%20detained%20her%2C%20to%20chants%20of%20%26quot%3Bshame%26quot%3B%20from%20onlookers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20showed%20a%20group%20of%20people%20in%20plain%20clothes%20removing%20flowers%20from%20a%20monument%20opposite%20the%20former%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Soviet%20secret%20police%2C%20while%20police%20blocked%20off%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20bridge%20next%20to%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20hooded%20men%20were%20seen%20scooping%20up%20flowers%20into%20bin%20bags%20that%20had%20been%20laid%20at%20an%20unofficial%20memorial%20to%20Navalny%20ally%2C%20dead%20Kremlin%20critic%20Boris%20Nemtsov.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20federal%20penitentiary%20service%20said%20Friday%20the%20Kremlin%20critic%20had%20died%20after%20he%20%26quot%3Bfelt%20bad%20after%20a%20walk%26quot%3B%20and%20lost%20consciousness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Navalny's%20lawyers%2C%20Leonid%20Solovyov%2C%20told%20the%20Novaya%20Gazeta%20newspaper%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20when%20another%20lawyer%20saw%20him%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20footage%20of%20a%20court%20hearing%20from%20his%20prison%20colony%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Navalny%20was%20seen%20smiling%20and%20joking%20as%20he%20addressed%20the%20judge%20by%20video%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I'm%20not%20afraid'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%2C%20who%20led%20street%20protests%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20became%20a%20household%20name%20through%20his%20anti-corruption%20campaigning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20exposes%20of%20official%20corruption%2C%20posted%20on%20his%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20racked%20up%20millions%20of%20views%20and%20brought%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Russians%20on%20to%20the%20streets%2C%20despite%20harsh%20anti-protest%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20jailed%20in%20early%202021%20after%20returning%20to%20Russia%20from%20Germany%2C%20where%20he%20was%20recovering%20from%20a%20near-fatal%20poisoning%20attack%20with%20Novichok%2C%20a%20Soviet-era%20nerve%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20subsequent%20investigation%20by%20his%20team%20and%20several%20media%20outlets%20said%20a%20Russian%20FSB%20hit%20squad%20was%20behind%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20his%20return%20he%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20barrage%20of%20charges%2C%20including%20a%2019-year%20prison%20sentence%20for%20%26quot%3Bextremism%26quot%3B%2C%20widely%20condemned%20by%20rights%20groups%20and%20seen%20in%20the%20West%20as%20retribution%20for%20his%20opposition%20to%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20decision%20to%20go%20back%20to%20Russia%20despite%20knowing%20he%20would%20face%20jail%20brought%20him%20global%20admiration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20afraid%20and%20I%20call%20on%20you%20not%20to%20be%20afraid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20appeal%20to%20supporters%20as%20he%20landed%20in%20Moscow%2C%20moments%20before%20being%20detained%20on%20charges%20linked%20to%20an%20old%20fraud%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20arrest%20spurred%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20demonstrations%20Russia%20had%20seen%20in%20decades%2C%20and%20thousands%20were%20detained%20at%20rallies%20nationwide%20calling%20for%20his%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Don't%20do%20nothing'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20behind%20bars%2C%20Navalny%20was%20a%20staunch%20opponent%20of%20Moscow's%20full-scale%20military%20offensive%20against%20Ukraine%20and%20was%20forced%20to%20watch%20on%2C%20helplessly%2C%20as%20the%20Kremlin%20dismantled%20his%20organisation%20and%20locked%20up%20his%20allies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20his%20top%20supporters%20fled%20into%20exile%20and%20continued%20to%20campaign%20against%20the%20offensive%20on%20Ukraine%20and%20repression%20inside%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20Navalny%20was%20moved%20to%20a%20remote%20Arctic%20prison%20colony%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BPolar%20Wolf%26quot%3B%20in%20Russia's%20Yamalo-Nenets%20region%20in%20northern%20Siberia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20in%20January%20that%20his%20daily%20routine%20included%20prison%20walks%20in%20freezing%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20being%20jailed%2C%20he%20spent%20more%20than%20300%20days%20in%20solitary%20confinement%2C%20where%20prison%20authorities%20kept%20him%20over%20alleged%20minor%20protocol%20infringements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20post%20on%20Navalny's%20Telegram%20channel%2C%20which%20he%20managed%20through%20his%20lawyers%20and%20team%20in%20exile%2C%20was%20a%20tribute%20to%20his%20wife%20posted%20on%20Valentine's%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20documentary%20filmed%20before%20he%20returned%20to%20Russia%2C%20Navalny%20was%20asked%20what%20message%20he%20wanted%20to%20leave%20to%20the%20Russian%20people%20sh