at's%20due%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20deterioration%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20US's%20financial%20situation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20national%20debt%20balance%20notched%20%2434%20trillion%20for%20the%20first%20time%20ever%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDollar%20dominance%20is%20here%20to%20stay%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20most%20dire%20threat%20to%20its%20status%20as%20the%20world's%20top%20reserve%20currency%20is%20actually%20the%20US%20economy%20itself%2C%20according%20to%20two%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteven%20Kamin%2C%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Fed's%20Division%20of%20International%20Finance%2C%20and%20Mark%20Sobel%2C%20a%20former%20Treasury%20Department%20economist%2C%20pointed%20to%20the%20dollar's%20long-running%20incumbency%20as%20the%20world's%20dominant%20currency%20in%20a%20new%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dollar%20is%20the%20most%20widely%20used%20currency%20in%20the%20world%20in%20both%20trade%20and%20central%20bank%20reserves%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20will%20likely%20stay%20that%20way%2C%20Kamin%20and%20Sobel%20said%2C%20since%20the%20use%20of%20the%20greenback%20outpaces%20other%20currencies%20by%20such%20a%20wide%20margin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dollar%20accounted%20for%20one%20side%20of%2088%25%20of%20all%20daily%20global%20trade%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20survey%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.bis.org%2Ftopics%2FDER%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20International%20Settlements%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20it%20accounted%20for%20around%2055%25%20of%20all%20central%20bank%20reserves%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20far%20more%20than%20any%20other%20foreign%20currency%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.imf.org%2F%3Fsk%3De6a5f467-c14b-4aa8-9f6d-5a09ec4e62a4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Monetary%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20commentators%20have%20warned%20a%20rival%20currency%20could%20soon%20displace%20the%20dollar.%20BRICS%20nations%20are%20already%20making%20efforts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdedollarization-dollar-dominance-brics-currrency-china-russia-trade-yuan-ruble-2023-12%5C%22%3Ephase%20the%20dollar%20out%20of%20trade%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20countries%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdollar-dominance-russia-china-rouble-yuan-brics-reserve-currency-imf-2022-6%5C%22%3ERussia%20and%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20proposed%20creating%20a%20new%20currency%20to%20challenge%20the%20greenback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20threats%20are%20in%20fact%20pretty%20tame%20compared%20to%20the%20threat%20to%20the%20dollar%20stemming%20from%20the%20US%20itself%2C%20Kamin%20and%20Sobel%20warned%2C%20citing%20the%20risk%20of%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20deterioration%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20US's%20financial%20and%20economic%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20political%20polarization%20of%20the%20country%2C%20the%20dysfunction%20of%20the%20US%20Congress%2C%20and%20the%20disinterest%20of%20politicians%20of%20all%20stripes%20in%20curbing%20the%20widening%20US%20budget%20deficit%2C%20this%20is%20hardly%20unthinkable%2C%26quot%3B%20Kamin%20and%20Sobel%20said%20of%20the%20dollar's%20potential%20dethroning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20should%20the%20result%20be%20a%20sustained%20rise%20in%20inflation%2C%20crowding%20out%20of%20private%20investment%2C%20heightened%20financial%20volatility%2C%20and%20reduction%20in%20the%20dynamism%20of%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20then%20the%20loss%20of%20dollar%20dominance%20would%20be%20the%20least%20of%20our%20worries.%20And%20those%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20risk%20stems%20from%20the%20fragmentation%20of%20global%20economies%20into%20separate%20blocs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26q