n%20phenomenon%20(his%20party%2C%20Renaissance%2C%20is%20just%20six%20years%20old).%C2%A0Marine%20Le%20Pen%2C%20a%20right-wing%20ultranationalist%20is%20the%20dominant%20voice%20of%20the%20disgruntled%20Opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20395px)%2085vw%2C%20395px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1.jpg%20781w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1-195x300.jpg%20195w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17141954%2F2024-India-In-Free-Fall_Cover-1-666x1024.jpg%20666w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697623%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22607%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E2024%3A%20India%20in%20Free%20Fall%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Sanjay%20Jha.%20Publisher%3A%20Harper%20Collins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20faces%20not%20just%20a%20strong%20BJP%20but%20a%20resurgent%20AAP%20in%20the%20national%20sweepstakes.%20The%20regional%20parties%20have%20virtually%20obliterated%20the%20Congress%20in%20several%20states%20like%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Bengal%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20etc.%20But%20the%20party%20still%20had%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20make%20a%20comeback.%20It%20needed%20a%20big%20idea.%20It%20needed%20a%20booster%20shot.%20And%20yet%2C%20ironically%20enough%2C%20anyone%20who%20wrote%20off%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20did%20so%20at%20great%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMyth%202%3A%20The%20BJP%20will%20lose%20on%20anti-incumbency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20above%20has%20been%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20boogeyman%20and%20has%20revealed%20its%20myopic%20underestimation%20of%20its%20rivals%E2%80%99%20doggedness.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20BJP%20is%20a%20ruthlessly%20efficient%20machine%20whose%20immoral%2C%20yet%20pugnacious%20attitude%20permeated%20through%20its%20organisational%20core.%20It%20had%20overcome%20several%20headwinds%20with%20aggressive%20campaigning%2C%20using%20an%20adroit%20mix%20of%20falsehoods%2C%20social%20polarisation%20and%20exaggerated%20successes%20sold%20over%20WhatsApp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20on%20the%20WHO%20estimates%20of%20Covid%20deaths%20in%20India%20being%20allegedly%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20at%2047%20lakh%20people%2C%20the%20BJP%20flattened%20the%20Congress%20instead%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20Western%20global%20conspiracy%20to%20malign%20India.%20It%20was%20absolutely%20ridiculous%2C%20but%20the%20Congress%20response%20was%20typically%20tepid.%20Secondly%2C%20anti-incumbency%20works%20more%20in%20two-party%20Western%20democracies%20like%20the%20US%20or%20UK%2C%20where%20there%20is%20always%20a%20visible%20and%20viable%20alternative%2C%20tried%20and%20trusted%2C%20on%20the%20national%20mainstream.%20Margaret%20Thatcher%2C%20Tony%20Blair%2C%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20Ronald%20Reagan%2C%20George%20Bush%20Jr%20had%20great%20runs%20that%20were%20abruptly%20terminated%2C%20because%20there%20was%20one%20clear%20option%20available.%20But%20in%20a%20multi-party%2C%20first-past-the-post%20system%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20beneficiaries%20of%20anti-incumbency%20through%20a%20splitting%20of%20votes%2C%20which%20neutralises%20the%20losses%20of%20the%20front%20runner%20Congress%20is%20waiting%20for%20Godot%20if%20it%20expects%20the%20BJP%20to%20just%20crumble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMyth%203%3A%20The%20Congress%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20default%20operating%20system.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Jaipur%20address%20in%202013%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20made%20a%20forthright%20disclosure%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20we%20win%20elections%2C%20but%20we%20do.%E2%80%9D%20Everyone%20guffawed%2C%20but%20they%20had%20misunderstood%20what%20was%20a%20loaded%20confession.%20Rahul%20had%20correctly%20identified%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20messy%20organisational%20functioning%2C%20a%20chaotic%20muddle%20despite%20electoral%20winnings%2C%20but%20unfortunately%2C%20he%20did%20not%20fix%20it.%20The%20problem%20was%20in%20the%20execution%20bug.%20Just%20like%20how%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20hit%20the%20nail%20on%20the%20head%20in%201985%20at%20the%20Congress%20centenary%20celebrations%20when%20he%20said%20that%2085%25%20of%20one%20rupee%20was%20being%20appropriated%20by%20greedy%20middlemen%2C%20with%20only%20the%20balance%2015%25%20reaching%20the%20ultimate%20beneficiary.%20Rajiv%20too%20did%20not%20or%20could%20not%20rigorously%20execute%20a%20robust%20counter-plan.%20It%20would%20end%20up%20becoming%20an%20albatross%20round%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20neck%2C%20a%20perfect%20example%20of%20how%20the%20path%20to%20hell%20is%20paved%20with%20good%20intentions.%20The%20Congress%20is%20a%20victim%20of%20the%20false%20belief%20that%20it%20is%20the%20natural%20party%20of%20governance.%20India%20has%20of%20late%20begun%20experimenting%20with%20different%20kinds%20of%20software.%20Winning%20elections%2C%20managing%20the%20political%20brand%20and%20retaining%20public%20trust%20requires%20a%20solid%20operating%20plan%20in%20the%205G%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Udaipur%20Declaration%20was%20important%3B%20it%20was%20an%20opportunity%20for%20renewal.%20The%20decision%20to%20rebut%20criticism%20of%20dynastic%20stranglehold%20by%20announcing%20a%20%E2%80%98one%20family%20one%20ticket%E2%80%99%20rule%20and%20the%20inclusion%20of%20%E2%80%98one%20person%20one%20post%E2%80%99%20augured%20well%20for%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20future.%20The%20Udaipur%20meet%20was%20a%20step%20forward%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20But%20if%20the%20Congress%20believed%20that%20the%20status%20of%20the%20principal%20leadership%20of%20the%20Opposition%20that%20it%20occupied%20would%20be%20its%20sole%20prerogative%2C%20it%20was%20being%20presumptuous.%20There%20were%20others%2C%20more%20ambitious%20and%20adrenaline-pumping%2C%20who%20were%20eyeing%20the%20vacant%20space%20that%20the%20Congress%20had%20conceded%20generously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20political%20colloquialism%2C%20whenever%20there%20is%20a%20striking%20departure%20of%20a%20senior%20leader%20(such%20as%20Sunil%20Jakhar%20in%20Punjab)%20or%20a%20mass%20exodus%20(as%20in%20Meghalaya%20MLAs%20of%20Congress%20joining%20Trinamool%20Congress)%2C%20the%20clich%C3%A9%20uttered%20is%20%E2%80%98the%20rats%20are%20deserting%20a%20sinking%20ship%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20partially%20true%2C%20the%20capsizing%20Titanic%20part%20of%20it.%20But%20calling%20them%20rodents%20may%20be%20an%20exaggeration.%20In%20India%2C%20ideological%20fidelity%20is%20an%20oxymoron%3B%20it%20has%20become%20purely%20transactional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20in%20India%20is%20defined%20not%20by%20its%20love%20for%20free%20markets%20and%20less%20government%2C%20but%20by%20its%20religious%20doctrine%20of%20extreme%20Hindutva%2C%20national%20security%2C%20restorative%20nostalgia%20and%20nativism.%20The%20Left%2C%20for%20its%20voluble%20sympathy%20for%20Maoist%20rebels%2C%20anti-Americanism%2C%20antediluvian%20communist%20de-growth%20model%20and%20minority%20protection.%20That%20leaves%20the%20centre%2C%20which%20had%20become%20India%E2%80%99s%20default%20option%20under%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20inclusive%20political%20umbrella%20since%20Pandit%20Nehru%20became%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20although%20it%20was%20always%20Left-leaning.%20But%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20multiple%20regional%20parties%2C%20each%20doing%20a%20copycat%20manifesto%20pledging%20commitment%20to%20secularism%2C%20socialism%20and%20social%20justice%2C%20it%20has%20become%20a%20crowded%20square.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20full%20advantage%20of%20this%20ideological%20amorphousness%20was%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Mamata%20Banerjee.%20Her%20target%3A%20the%20severely%20depleted%20Congress%20party.%20The%20reason%20why%20many%20Congress%20leaders%20(L.%20Faleiro%2C%20Sushmita%20Dev%2C%20Kirti%20Azad%2C%20etc.)%20were%20merrily%20dancing%20to%20Didi%E2%80%99s%20drumbeat%20was%20because%20joining%20TMC%20was%20not%20causing%20a%20bitter%20heartburn%20unlike%20Congress%2C%20which%20was%20playing%20footsie%20with%20its%20%E2%80%98communal%20nemesis%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20BJP.%20Joining%20TMC%20was%20akin%20to%20leaving%20Facebook%20for%20WhatsApp%3B%20one%20was%20still%20part%20of%20the%20Metaverse.%20Banerjee%20was%20hoping%20that%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20market%20valuation%20would%20soon%20tip%20over%20that%20of%20the%20mothership%20itself.%20Her%20comment%20in%20Mumbai%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20UPA%E2%80%9D%20(after%20meeting%20Sharad%20Pawar%20and%20Sanjay%20Raut)%20was%20a%20sardonic%20assault%20on%20the%20Congress.%20TMC%20was%20creating%20an%20alternative%20arrangement.%20It%20wanted%20to%20lead%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp-300x162.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04121914%2FF6AYMqwXkAAlspp-1024x553.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683467%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22648%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40MamataOfficial%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Pawan%20Varma%2C%20former%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20called%20me%20and%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20private%20chat%2C%20I%20kind%20of%20figured%20out%20what%20he%20had%20in%20mind.%20Varma%2C%20who%20is%20an%20astute%20debater%20and%20a%20Stephanian%20wordsmith%2C%20did%20no%20pussyfooting%3B%20%E2%80%9CJoin%20the%20TMC%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20Congress%20has%20become%20spiritless%2C%20limp%2C%20old%20fogey%2C%20was%20what%20he%20told%20me.%20TMC%2C%20under%20Mamata%20had%20the%20roar%20of%20a%20hungry%20tiger.%20TMC%20would%20be%20the%20new%20INC%3B%20a%20combative%2C%20strategic%2C%20streetfighter%20party%20that%20could%20defeat%20the%20BJP.%20The%20Goa%20assembly%20results%20would%20establish%20that%20paradigm.%20Verma%2C%20when%20he%20speaks%20in%20his%20deep%20baritone%20voice%2C%20making%20a%20persuasive%20argument%20which%20he%20considers%20ironclad%2C%20can%20even%20convince%20a%20lion%20to%20befriend%20a%20goat.%20I%20heard%20him%20out%20and%20promised%20to%20call%20him%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20was%20understandable%20that%20Congress%20targeted%20the%20BJP%20relentlessly%20given%20their%20historical%20rivalry%2C%20it%20made%20the%20cardinal%20mistake%20of%20underestimating%20its%20knavish%20allies%20or%20ex-Congressmen.%20It%20had%20ignored%20its%20own%20political%20history.%20The%20Jana%20Sangh%2FBJP%E2%80%99s%20meteoric%20rise%20began%20after%20the%20Congress%20was%20first%20damaged%20by%20non-BJP%20regional%20formations%3A%20The%20Janata%20Party%20in%201977%20(Jayaprakash%20Narayan)%2C%20V.P.%20Singh%20in%201989%2C%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20and%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20following%20the%20Mandal%20agitations.%20The%20Mandal%20agitation%20damaged%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20support%20base.%20A%20bruised%20Congress%20then%20ceded%20substantial%20space%20to%20an%20industrious%20BJP%20which%20stepped%20up%20on%20aggressive%20majoritarianism%20using%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20agitation%20and%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20judgement%20to%20further%20cripple%20the%20slumbering%20centrist%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20larger%20RSS%20family%2C%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%2C%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20controversy%20came%20at%20an%20opportune%20time.%20Already%20facing%20heat%20from%20Muslim%20conservatives%2C%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20now%20faced%20heat%20from%20Hindutva%20groups%20as%20well.%20The%20increasingly%20militant%20Hindutva%20groups%20got%20a%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20in%20February%20when%20the%20district%20court%20in%20Faizabad%20ordered%20the%20disputed%20site%20to%20be%20unlocked%20and%20allowed%20the%20public%20to%20pray%20at%20the%20spot.%20This%20seemingly%20small%20concession%20was%20to%20prove%20expensive%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETMC%E2%80%99s%20new%20outreach%2C%20which%20was%20curated%20by%20Prashant%20Kishor%2C%20was%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20Congress%20faced%20because%20of%20a%20serious%20internal%20erosion%20since%201989.TMC%20had%20an%20ambitious%20destination%3A%20to%20become%20the%20second%20largest%20political%20party%20(propelling%20Didi%20to%20become%20prime%20minister%20in%20a%20hung%20Parliament%20situation).%20Discerning%20observers%20would%20have%20noticed%20that%20it%20had%20already%20checkmated%20the%20BJP%20by%20doing%20a%20reverse%20migration%20of%20leaders%20back%20to%20the%20TMC%20after%20their%20hurricane%20sweep%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%202022.%20At%20stake%20is%2042%20Lok%20Sabha%20(LS)%20seats%20in%20Bengal%3B%20the%20Congress%20has%2052%20LS%20seats%20pan-India.%20If%20the%20TMC%20swept%20Bengal%20and%20the%20Congress%20stagnated%20or%20dipped%2C%20anything%20was%20possible%3Cem%3E.%20The%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3E(it%20has%20endorsed%20Congress%20in%20practically%20every%20general%20election)%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20next%20general%20election%20is%20about%20three%20years%20away.%20It%20is%20not%20too%20late%20for%20Congress%20to%20become%20a%20big-tent%20national%20party%20capable%20of%20representing%20all%20Indians%2C%20as%20its%20founders%20intended.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishor%20may%20have%20made%20one%20fatal%20miscalculation%20in%20his%20Operation%20Mamata%3A%20his%20assumption%20that%20the%20Congress%20would%20just%20wither%20away%2C%20succumbing%20meekly%20to%20his%20grandiose%20designs.%20He%20had%20on%20the%20contrary%20awakened%20the%20sleepy%2C%20somnolent%20giant.%20Two%20developments%20gave%20a%20hint%20of%20an%20unusually%20combative%20Congress.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20Congress%20promptly%20reassembled%20its%20traditional%20allies%20like%20DMK%2C%20National%20Conference%20and%20CPI(M)%2C%20in%20a%20quick%20bid%20to%20nip%20the%20TMC%20enterprise%20in%20the%20bud.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20joining%20them%20were%20also%20both%20NCP%20and%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20who%20had%20momentarily%20buoyed%20TMC%20hearts.%20Realpolitik%20is%20never%20linear.%20Congress%20President%20Sonia%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20not%20invite%20TMC%20even%20as%20a%20perfunctory%20gesture%20for%20a%20dinner%20meeting%20at%20her%20home%20was%20a%20declaration%20of%20war.%20Secondly%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20threw%20a%20curveball%20at%20the%20BJP%2C%20by%20belatedly%20biting%20the%20bullet%20on%20the%20Hinduism%20vs%20Hindutva%20debate.%20It%20is%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20that%20the%20Congress%20has%20imprudently%20dodged%20with%20disastrous%20results%20for%20too%20long.%20It%20showed%20a%20rare%20pragmatic%20risk-taking%20by%20the%20young%20Gandhi%20scion.%20Judging%20by%20initial%20reactions%20from%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%2C%20the%20BJP%20appeared%20threatened%2C%20at%20least%20temporarily.%20Rahul%20was%20still%20the%20only%20Opposition%20leader%20who%20made%20the%20BJP%20squirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%20early%202022%20in%20UP%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Goa%2C%20Manipur%20and%20Uttarakhand%20led%20to%20further%20decimation%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20it%20did%20not%20mean%20that%20TMC%20would%20find%20replacing%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20as%20main%20Opposition%20voice%2C%20a%20slam-dunk%20operation.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20Kishor%20had%20inadvertently%20rekindled%20the%20Congress.%20The%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Goa%20experiment%20was%20a%20complete%20fiasco%2C%20and%20with%20that%20brief%20flirtation%20with%20a%20pan-India%20power%20pitch%2C%20it%20abandoned%20its%20national%20aspirations%2C%20sticking%20to%20the%20more%20familiar%20Northeastern%20states.%20The%20BJP%20benefitted%20from%20the%20split%20votes.%20The%20Congress%20lost%20again%2C%20but%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20still%20hold%20on%20to%2024%25%20of%20the%20votes%20and%20get%2011%20seats%20in%20the%2040%20seats%20state%20assembly%20left%20no%20one%20in%20doubt%20as%20to%20who%20the%20real%20Congress%20was%2C%20warts%20and%20all%20had%20woken%20up%20at%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20call%20PawanVerma%20back.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20he%20expected%20me%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjay%20Jha%20is%20a%20former%20national%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20party.%20He%20also%20worked%20as%20a%20banker%20and%20an%20internet%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708160364000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmyth-and-reality-about-congress-partys-strength-in-a-changed-political-context%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Congress%20leader%20Sanjay%20Jha%20in%20his%20forthcoming%20book%20talks%20about%20how%20politics%20has%20changed%20under%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20and%20the%20weakening%20of%20Congress%20party%20since%202014.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmyth-and-reality-about-congress-partys-strength-in-a-changed-political-context%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ten%20wagons%20of%20goods%20train%20derail%2C%20overturn%20near%20Zakhira%20flyover%20in%20Delhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708159565000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-08%2F11%2Ffull%2F1660193829-8368.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Ften-wagons-of-goods-train-derail-overturn-near-zakhira-flyover-in-delhi-124021700279_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Around%20ten%20wagons%20of%20a%20goods%20train%20derailed%20and%20overturned%20on%20the%20Patel%20Nagar-Dayabasti%20section%20in%20the%20Delhi%20area%20on%20Saturday%20morning%2C%20officials%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Ften-wagons-of-goods-train-derail-overturn-near-zakhira-flyover-in-delhi-124021700279_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Ften-wagons-of-goods-train-derail-overturn-near-zakhira-flyover-in-delhi-124021700279_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Ften-wagons-of-goods-train-derail-overturn-near-zakhira-flyover-in-delhi-124021700279_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Solution%20to%20Farmers'%20Problems%20Lies%20in%20the%20Macro%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16094308%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-9.40.44-AM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20strife%20between%20the%20government%20and%20farm%20unions%20has%20again%20come%20to%20a%20head%20with%20farmers%20heading%20towards%20Delhi%20more%20than%20three%20years%20after%20the%202021%20episode.%20The%20issues%20this%20time%20are%20somewhat%20different%20from%20those%20in%202021-22.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20issue%20was%20the%20repeal%20of%20stealthily%20enacted%20three%20farm%20laws.%20Now%20the%20key%20issue%20is%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20incomes%20via%20a%20legally%20guaranteed%20MSP%20(Minimum%20Support%20Price)%20for%20all%20crops.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELinked%20to%20this%20are%20the%20demand%20for%20debt%20waiver%2C%20pension%2C%20additional%20provision%20for%20MGNREGS%2C%20etc.%20The%20farmers%20have%20also%20widened%20the%20ambit%20of%20their%20protest%20by%20including%20rural%20employment%20and%20issues%20pertaining%20to%20indigenous%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFocus%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20key%20point%20is%20inadequate%20incomes%20of%20a%20vast%20majority%20farmers%20(85%25)%20who%20have%20marginal%20or%20small%20holding%2C%20plowing%20less%20than%202%20hectares%20of%20land.%20Even%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20farmers%20supplement%20their%20income%20from%20agriculture%20through%20other%20work%20or%20business%2C%20like%20agri-businesses.%20Thus%2C%20even%20if%20the%20Punjab%20farmers%20have%20taken%20the%20lead%2C%20they%20represent%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20farming%20community.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20talks%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20between%20the%20government%20and%20the%20farm%20leaders%20having%20failed%2C%20the%20farmers%20decided%20to%20march%20to%20Delhi.%20Trust%20between%20the%20government%20and%20the%20farmers%20is%20almost%20non-existent%20since%20the%20promises%20made%20in%202022%20when%20the%20farmers%20lifted%20their%20siege%20of%20the%20Capital%20have%20not%20been%20kept.%20The%20doubling%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20incomes%20by%202022%20is%20also%20nowhere%20in%20sight.%20A%20Committee%2C%20set%20up%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20issue%20of%20MSP%20and%20reforms%20in%20agriculture%20became%20suspect%20since%20it%20was%20packed%20with%20pro-government%20members%20and%20therefore%20boycotted%20by%20the%20farm%20unions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGovernment%E2%80%99s%20arguments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20is%20the%20government%20against%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20principal%20demand%20%E2%80%93%20MSP%20for%20all%20crops%20based%20on%20full%20cost%3F%20The%20farmers%20feel%20this%20is%20the%20only%20way%20they%20can%20turn%20the%20currently%20loss%20making%20proposition%20into%20a%20profitable%20one.%20Then%20the%20other%20demands%2C%20like%2C%20debt%20waiver%20would%20lose%20their%20urgency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20arguments%20advanced%20against%20this%20proposition%20are%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a)%20it%20will%20be%20hugely%20expensive%2C%20costing%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20crore.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20cost%20was%20put%20at%20Rs.%2027%20lakh%20crore%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eb)%20The%20entire%20crop%20would%20have%20to%20be%20procured%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ec)%20This%20would%20not%20be%20administratively%20feasible%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ed)%20Private%20traders%20would%20stop%20buying%20and%20the%20farmers%20would%20lose%20out%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20e)%20Currently%2C%20only%20wheat%20and%20paddy%20are%20being%20procured%20so%20how%20can%20MSP%20be%20implemented%20in%20the%20case%20of%20other%20crops%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20f)%20Only%20the%20big%20farmers%20get%20the%20MSP%3B%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eg)%20Difficulties%20will%20mount%20in%20WTO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FiIwcv7walvY%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22'MSP%20Applies%20to%20Only%2010%25%20of%20Agri%20Households%3B%20Hike%20Farmers%20Want%20Will%20Raise%20Food%20Inflation%20By%2025-30%25'%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20facts%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMSP%20is%20applicable%20to%2023%20crops%20and%20implemented%20only%20for%20wheat%20and%20paddy.%20There%20is%20also%20an%20assured%20price%20for%20sugarcane%20to%20be%20paid%20by%20the%20sugar%20mills.%20So%2C%20these%20three%20crops%20assure%20a%20profit%20which%20other%20crops%20do%20not.%20Hence%20cropping%20pattern%20has%20shifted%20in%20favour%20of%20these%20three%20crops.%20Consequently%2C%20crops%20that%20suit%20a%20agro-climatic%20zone%20are%20not%20grown%20there%20resulting%20in%20environmental%20damage.%20Like%2C%20cultivating%20sugarcane%20in%20water%20starved%20areas%20of%20Maharashtra%20and%20paddy%20in%20Punjab.%20The%20result%20is%20excess%20production%20of%20these%20three%20crops%2C%20large%20stocks%20with%20the%20government%20and%20much%20wastage%20since%20there%20is%20inadequate%20storage%20capacity.%20The%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%20has%20been%20heavily%20subsidized%20for%20procuring%20and%20holding%20the%20stock%20and%20releasing%20it%20in%20the%20Public%20Distribution%20System%20(PDS).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20MSP%20is%20implemented%20for%20all%20crops%2C%20profitability%20would%20be%20the%20same%20across%20all%20of%20them%20and%20crops%20would%20be%20grown%20based%20on%20their%20suitability%20in%20a%20given%20agro-climatic%20zone.%20That%20would%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a)%20Eliminate%20excess%20stocks%20of%20some%20crops%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eb)%20Reduce%20need%20for%20large%20storage%20capacity%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20c)%20Increase%20production%20of%20those%20crops%2C%20which%20currently%20are%20in%20short%20supply%2C%20like%2C%20oilseeds%3B%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ed)%20Reduce%20if%20not%20end%20import%20of%20these%20crops%20resulting%20in%20saving%20of%20foreign%20exchange.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20storage%20space%20released%20would%20become%20available%20for%20other%20crops.%20The%20subsidy%20to%20FCI%20would%20drastically%20decline%20and%20food%20wastage%20would%20be%20reduced.%20As%20crops%20suited%20to%20the%20agro-climatic%20conditions%20would%20be%20grown%2C%20environmental%20damage%20would%20decline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20argument%20that%20the%20entire%20crop%20would%20have%20to%20be%20procured%20to%20implement%20MSP%20is%20fallacious.%20Procurement%20would%20be%20required%20only%20when%20the%20price%20drops%20below%20MSP%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20at%20the%20margin.%20As%20excess%20production%20declines%2C%20the%20price%20of%20the%20crops%20would%20rise%20above%20the%20MSP.%20If%20the%20government%20were%20to%20procure%20the%20entire%20crop%20and%20store%20it%20there%20would%20be%20mass%20starvation%20and%20sky%20high%20prices.%20Whatever%20the%20government%20procures%20would%20get%20sold%20in%20the%20market%2C%20so%20it%20would%20only%20need%20working%20capital%20which%20would%20be%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20Rs.10%20lakh%20crore%20bandied%20about.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20would%20be%20a%20win-win%20situation.%20So%2C%20why%20is%20the%20government%20reluctant%20to%20implement%20the%20scheme%3F%20It%20wants%20food%20prices%20to%20remain%20low%20so%20that%20workers%20can%20be%20paid%20a%20low%20wage%20which%20would%20lead%20to%20higher%20profit%20for%20businesses%20and%20benefit%20the%20elite%20which%20needs%20cheap%20labour%20(servants%2C%20drivers%2C%20etc.)%20to%20maintain%20its%20comfortable%20life%20style.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15145529%2F9313A034-D5C5-4DE6-A64D-6FDBEE5AE65D-1-1024x768.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15145529%2F9313A034-D5C5-4DE6-A64D-6FDBEE5AE65D-1-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15145529%2F9313A034-D5C5-4DE6-A64D-6FDBEE5AE65D-1-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15145529%2F9313A034-D5C5-4DE6-A64D-6FDBEE5AE65D-1.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697315%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFarmers%20protesting%20in%20Rajpura%20railway%20station%20in%20Punjab.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20Arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EReform%20needed%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20do%20farm%20produce%20prices%20drop%20below%20the%20MSP%3F%20Price%20of%20agricultural%20produce%20is%20demand%20and%20supply%20determined%20because%20there%20are%20a%20huge%20number%20of%20producers%20and%20any%20mismatch%20between%20them%20leads%20to%20price%20changes.%20For%20instance%2C%20supply%20floods%20in%20during%20the%20post-harvest%20period%20ad%20prices%20drop.%20Further%2C%20NHFS%20data%20shows%20that%2030%25%20women%20and%20children%20are%20malnourished.%20They%20are%20not%20able%20to%20afford%20proper%20nutrition%20in%20spite%20of%20government%20providing%20almost%20free%20food%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20implication%20is%20that%20overall%20demand%20is%20low%20due%20to%20large%20scale%20poverty%20and%20that%20is%20why%2C%20farmers%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20a%20remunerative%20price.%20An%20OECD%20study%20estimates%20that%20the%20loss%20to%20Indian%20farmers%20in%202022%20due%20to%20lower%20price%20was%20Rs%2014%20lakh%20crore.%20This%20is%203.5%20times%20the%20subsidy%20to%20farmers.%20That%20is%20why%20MSP%2C%20procurement%20and%20public%20distribution%20become%20crucial.%20If%20workers%20and%20farmers%20had%20a%20civilised%20existence%2C%20these%20would%20not%20be%20needed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20constitution%20promises%20a%20%E2%80%98living%20wage%E2%80%99%20to%20all.%20If%20that%20is%20ensured%2C%20demand%20for%20farm%20produce%20would%20rise%20both%20from%20workers%20and%20farmers%20and%20that%20would%20drive%20prices%20of%20agricultural%20produce%20above%20the%20MSP.%20So%2C%20workers%20are%20the%20natural%20allies%20of%20the%20farmers%20and%20the%20farmers%20ought%20to%20demand%20and%20pay%20them%20a%20%E2%80%98living%20wage%E2%80%99.%20The%20farmers%20would%20not%20lose%20even%20after%20paying%20a%20higher%20wage%20since%20their%20MSP%20would%20be%20determined%20accordingly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHigher%20wages%20and%20prices%20would%20lead%20to%20higher%20inflation%20which%20could%20be%20tackled%20by%20reducing%20indirect%20taxes%20and%20raising%20direct%20taxes.%20In%20the%20alternative%20scenario%20presented%20above%2C%20farm%20subsidies%20would%20decline%20and%20that%20would%20help%20in%20WTO%20negotiations.%20Subsidies%20can%20be%20shifted%20to%20education%2C%20health%2C%20public%20distribution%20system%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20etc.%2C%20so%20that%20neither%20the%20%E2%80%98living%20wage%E2%80%99%20nor%20the%20MSP%20need%20rise%20unduly.%20The%20result%20of%20all%20this%20would%20be%20a%20virtuous%20cycle%20of%20increase%20in%20employment%20and%20demand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findias-wto-stance-on-farmers-will-be-a-test-of-its-rhetoric-of-championing-the-global-south%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20WTO%20Stance%20on%20Farmers%20Will%20Be%20a%20Test%20of%20Its%20Rhetoric%20of%20Championing%20the%20Global%20South%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsidies%20are%20said%20to%20be%20undesirable.%20That%20is%20not%20the%20case%20for%20education%20and%20health%20which%20are%20cases%20of%20merit%20wants%20or%20in%20case%20of%20infrastructure%2C%20like%2C%20communication%20and%20transportation.%20The%20government%20gives%20subsidies%20to%20industry%20and%20calls%20them%20incentives.%20Take%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20which%20offers%20heavy%20subsidies%20to%20big%20corporations%20who%20really%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20them.%20These%20are%20called%20%E2%80%98tax%20expenditures%E2%80%99%20which%20in%202021%20amounted%20to%20Rs%204.48%20lakh%20crores.%20Subsidies%20are%20offered%20on%20land%2C%20water%20and%20electricity%20to%20businesses.%20So%2C%20why%20the%20partiality%20towards%20the%20already%20well%20off%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20argued%20that%20farmers%20should%20take%20up%20employment%20in%20non-agriculture.%20But%2C%20employment%20is%20hardly%20available%20in%20organised%20non-agriculture%20due%20to%20mechanisation%2C%20automation%20and%20now%20use%20of%20AI.%20The%20per%20worker%20output%20in%20the%20organised%20sector%20is%2019%20times%20that%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%20So%2C%20as%20the%20former%20expands%20due%20to%20concessions%20given%20to%20it%2C%20overall%20employment%20contracts.%20Workers%20have%20to%20resort%20to%20self-employment%20at%20low%20wages%20or%20remain%20disguised%20unemployed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20objections%20raised%20against%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20demands%20are%20only%20scare%20crows%20to%20frighten%20the%20public.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20solution%20to%20farmers%E2%80%99%20problems%20of%20low%20incomes%20lies%20in%20macro%2C%20due%20to%20the%20linkages%20between%20output%2C%20income%20distribution%2C%20prices%2C%20employment%20and%20investment.%20This%20will%20provide%20a%20rational%20long%20term%20policy.%20Piecemeal%20and%20ad%20hoc%20policies%20attempted%20till%20now%20have%20resulted%20in%20contradictions%20and%20persisting%20poverty.%20Of%20late%2C%20farmers%20in%20Europe%20have%20also%20been%20blocking%20roads%20and%20highways%20to%20rise%20their%20demands.%20Clearly%2C%20post%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20adequate%20farm%20incomes%20has%20become%20more%20acute%20globally.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20big%20policy%20shift%20would%20take%20a%20few%20years%20to%20fully%20get%20implemented.%20Poverty%20and%20inadequate%20demand%20need%20to%20be%20tackled%20by%20policy%20makers%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20vast%20majority%20and%20not%20just%20of%20businesses%20and%20the%20well-off.%20The%20issue%20is%20political%2C%20and%20judges%20whether%20the%20life%20style%20of%20the%20latter%20should%20be%20maintained%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20former.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EArun%20Kumar%20is%20retired%20professor%20of%20economics%2C%20JNU.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20I%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Endian%20Economy%E2%80%99s%20Greatest%20Crisis%3A%20The%20Impact%20of%20Coronavirus%20and%20the%20Road%20Ahead%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708158781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16094308%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-9.40.44-AM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fthe-solution-to-farmers-problems-lies-in-the-macro%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Poverty%20and%20inadequate%20demand%20need%20to%20be%20tackled%20by%20policy%20makers%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20vast%20majority%20and%20not%20just%20of%20businesses%20and%20the%20well-off.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fthe-solution-to-farmers-problems-lies-in-the-macro%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taiwan%20signs%20migrant%20worker%20MoU%20with%20India%2C%20seen%20as%20new%20source%20of%20labour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708157835000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-02%2F17%2Ffull%2F1708157713-8601.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ftaiwan-signs-migrant-worker-mou-with-india-seen-as-new-source-of-labour-124021700289_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ministry%20will%20formally%20notify%20lawmakers%20of%20the%20MOU%20and%20hold%20follow-up%20meetings%20with%20Indian%20officials%2C%20according%20to%20the%20statement%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ftaiwan-signs-migrant-worker-mou-with-india-seen-as-new-source-of-labour-124021700289_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ftaiwan-signs-migrant-worker-mou-with-india-seen-as-new-source-of-labour-124021700289_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ftaiwan-signs-migrant-worker-mou-with-india-seen-as-new-source-of-labour-124021700289_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20MSP%2C%20Modi%20Government%20Must%20Display%20Maturity%20and%20Give%20Farmers%20Their%20Due%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27210340%2FEffect.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%C2%A0key%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Ffarmers-protest-msp-guarantee-law-9157499%2F%5C%22%3Edemands%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98Dilli%20Chalo%E2%80%99%20march%20is%20a%20legal%20guarantee%20of%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP).%20The%20government%20is%20fuelling%20a%20media-linked%20narrative%20to%20confuse%20people%20that%20guaranteeing%20MSP%20would%20add%20to%20the%20fiscal%20cost%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%2C%20how%20during%20the%20year-long%20Kisan%20Andolan%2C%20a%20guaranteed%20MSP%20was%20one%20of%20the%20two%20main%20demands%20made%20by%20protesting%20farmers%20then.%20The%20first%20was%20for%20repealing%20the%20three-agri%20reform%20laws%20and%20the%20second%20was%20to%20provide%20a%20legal%20guarantee%20on%20MSP.%20While%20the%20Modi%20government%20ultimately%20conceded%20to%20the%20first%2C%20it%20never%20committed%20to%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20can%20MSP%20be%20made%20legally%20binding%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Harish%20Damodaran%20explains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%C2%A0there%20are%20two%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20MSP%20can%20be%20made%20legally%20binding%20for%20the%20government.%20The%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20to%20force%20private%20buyers%20to%20pay%20it.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20no%20crop%20can%20be%20purchased%20below%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Feveryday-explainers%2Ffarmers-crops-price-msp-explained-7789563%2F%5C%22%3EMSP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20also%20act%20as%20the%20floor%20price%20for%20bidding%20in%20mandi%20auctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20already%20a%20precedent%20for%20private%20players%20to%20pay%20for%20MSP%3A%20In%20sugarcane%2C%20mills%20are%20required%20by%20law%20to%20pay%20growers%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cfair%20and%20remunerative%20price%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Haryana%20fix%20even%20higher%20state%20advised%20prices%20%E2%80%93%20within%2014%20days%20of%20supply.%20In%20no%20other%20crop%20is%20the%20compulsion%20to%20pay%20the%20government-announced%20MSP%20thrust%20on%20the%20private%20trade%2Findustry%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Esecond%20%3C%2Fem%3Eroute%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20government%20itself%20buying%20the%20entire%20crop%20that%20farmers%20offer%20at%20the%20MSP.%20This%20would%20mean%20an%20added%20fiscal%20cost%20for%20the%20government%20to%20pay%20for%20this%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Eat%20a%20time%20when%20it%20has%20clearly%20prioritised%20capex-based%20expenditure%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20social%20welfare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20farm%20subsidies%2C%20and%20other%20essential%20scheme-based%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202019-20%2C%20before%20the%20Andolan%2C%20government%20agencies%20like%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%2C%20National%20Agricultural%20Cooperative%20Marketing%20Federation%20of%20India%20and%20Cotton%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(CCI)%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Eprocured%2077.34%20million%20tonnes%20(mt)%20of%20paddy%20and%2038.99%20mt%20of%20wheat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20worth%20roughly%20Rs%20140%2C834%20crore%20and%20Rs%2075%2C060%20crore%20at%20their%20respective%20MSPs.%20Further%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Ethey%20purchased%20105.23%20lakh%20bales%20of%20cotton%3C%2Fa%3E%20(MSP%20value%20of%20Rs%2028%2C202%20crore%20in%20terms%20of%20raw%20un-ginned%20kapas)%2C%202.1%20mt%20of%20chana%20or%20chickpea%20(Rs%2010%2C238%20crore)%2C%200.7%20mt%20each%20of%20arhar%20or%20pigeon-pea%20(Rs%204%2C176%20crore)%20and%20groundnut%20(Rs%203%2C614%20crore)%2C%200.8%20mt%20of%20rapeseed-mustard%20(Rs%203%2C540%20crore)%20and%200.1%20mt%20of%20moong%20or%20green%20gram%20(Rs%20987%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20put%20facts%20into%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20is%20projecting%20that%20a%20guaranteed%20MSP%20would%20make%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FHartoshSinghBal%2Fstatus%2F1758010357606465754%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ecost%20by%20Rs%2017%20lakh%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20figure%20is%20incorrect%20and%20the%20argument%20remains%20absurd%20for%20any%20logical%20reason.%20The%20actual%20cost%20of%20running%20an%20MSP%20backed%20by%20the%20government%20payout%20as%20part%20of%20a%20targeted%20scheme%20or%20a%20price%20stabilisation%20fund%20may%20not%20be%20more%20than%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crore.%20Yogendra%20Yadav%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Fcan-india-actually-afford-msp-for-farmers-its-a-question-of-political-will%2F588793%2F%5C%22%3Eexplained%20in%20this%20excellent%20piece%3C%2Fa%3E%20(back%20in%202021)%20how%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20actually%20help%20farmers%20with%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20explained%20through%20this%20chart%20illustrated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20MSP%20value%20of%20the%20total%20production%20of%20the%2023%20crops%20(for%20which%20MSP%20is%20currently%20provided)%20worked%20out%20to%20around%20Rs%2010.78%20lakh%20crore%20in%202019-20.%20Not%20all%20this%20produce%20is%20marketed.%20Farmers%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Eretain%20part%20of%20it%20for%20self-consumption%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seed%20for%20the%20next%20season%E2%80%99s%20sowing%2C%20and%20also%20for%20feeding%20their%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20marketed%20surplus%20ratio%20for%20different%20crops%20is%20estimated%20to%20range%20from%20below%2050%25%20for%20ragi%20and%2065-70%25%20for%20bajra%20(pearl-millet)%20and%20jowar%20(sorghum)%20to%2075%25%20for%20wheat%2C%2080%25%20for%20paddy%2C%2085%25%20for%20sugarcane%2C%2090%25%20for%20most%20pulses%2C%20and%2095%25-plus%20for%20cotton%2C%20jute%2C%20soyabean%20and%20sunflower.%20Taking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Ean%20average%20of%2075%25%20would%20yield%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20number%20of%20just%20over%20Rs%208%20lakh%20crore.%20This%20is%20the%20MSP%20value%20of%20production%2C%20calculated%20by%20Damodaran%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-the-cost-of-guaranteed-msp-7157934%2F%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20is%20the%20marketable%20surplus-which%20farmers%20actually%20sell%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20as%20if%20the%20government%20is%20required%20to%20pay%20any%20substantial%20additional%20fiscal%20cost%20to%20incur%20this%2C%20given%20it%20is%20already%20procuring%20paddy%2C%20wheat%2C%20cotton%2C%20pulses%2C%20oilseeds%2C%20etc.(from%20the%2023%20crops%20list)%20at%20MSP.%20Moreover%2C%20as%20done%20for%20sugarcane%20(in%20the%20cited%20reference%20above)%2C%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20State%20Governments%20can%20ask%20private%20firms%2Fbuyers%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20MSP%20from%20what%20they%20buy%2Fsource%20directly%20from%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20iterating%20how%20due%20to%20the%20middle-man%20profiteering%20practices%20seen%20in%20the%20retail%20marketing%20of%20crops%2C%20across%20Indian%20cities%2C%20the%20farmers%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20the%20fair%20share%20of%20return%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98high%20price%E2%80%99%20at%20which%20crops%2C%20vegetables%2C%20or%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20produce%20is%20sold%20in%20the%20urban%20market.%20The%20rising%20urban%20consumer%20bias%2C%20and%20a%20higher%20willingness%20to%20pay%20amongst%20upper%20middle-income%20groups%20and%20richer%20classes%20help%20in%20the%20middle-man%20(intermediary)%20profiteering%20of%20farm%20goods%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20farmer%20welfare%2C%20which%20is%20why%20farmers%20in%20rural%20areas%20need%20more%20price-based%20protection%20via%20MSP%20(richer%20farmers%20of%20states%20like%20Haryana%20and%20Punjab%20have%20made%20the%20government%20more%20accountable%20in%20ensuring%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20concern%20on%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20apathy%20towards%20farmer%20interests%20goes%20beyond%20politics%20alone%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fbudget-2023-is-optimistic-but-indifferent-to-past-failures%5C%22%3Eis%20more%20structural%20to%20the%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20misplaced%20budgetary%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fbudget-2023-is-optimistic-but-indifferent-to-past-failures%5C%22%3Ea%20silent%20fiscal%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20government%20has%20been%20experiencing%20for%20some%20time%20now%20(where%20it%20has%20often%20failed%20to%20collect%20the%20revenue%20it%20outlays%20for%20in%20the%20budgetary%20estimates).%20This%20has%20made%20it%20even%20less%20keen%20to%20support%20farmers%20on%20issues%20like%20MSP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20fiscal%20priority%20attributed%20to%20essential%20spending%20on%20programs%20of%20farm-based%20subsidies%20and%20existing%20costs%2C%20budgeted%20in%20the%20Union%20budgets%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fbudget%2Fnews%2Frecord-10th-anti-farmer-anti-people-budget-in-a-row-says-kisan-union-124020102017_1.html%5C%22%3Eoverall%20allocations%20for%20agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20allied%20activities%2C%20there%20is%20a%20decline%20of%2022.3%25%20compared%20to%20actual%20expenditure%20in%202022-23%20and%20a%206%25%20decline%20vis%20a%20vis%20the%202023-24%20revised%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20All%20India%20Kisan%20Sabha%20(AIKS)%20after%20the%20recent%20Interim%20Union%20budget%20criticised%20the%20Modi%20government%20for%20passing%20an%20anti-farmer-centric%20budget%20for%20the%2010%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20time%20in%20a%20row.%20AIKS%20argued%20how%20there%20has%20been%20no%20allocation%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20long-standing%20demand%20of%20the%20farmers%20for%20ensuring%20Minimum%20Support%20Prices%20as%20per%20the%20C2%2B50%25%20estimates%20becomes%20a%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fbudget%2Fnews%2Frecord-10th-anti-farmer-anti-people-budget-in-a-row-says-kisan-union-124020102017_1.html%5C%22%3Eallocation%20for%20fertiliser%20subsidy%20in%202024-25%20is%20Rs%2087%2C339%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20than%20the%20actual%20expenditure%20in%202022-23.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fbudget%2Fnews%2Frecord-10th-anti-farmer-anti-people-budget-in-a-row-says-kisan-union-124020102017_1.html%5C%22%3Eallocation%20for%20food%20subsidy%20is%20Rs%206%2C%207552%20crore%20less%20than%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20actual%20expenditure%20in%202022-23.%20This%20was%20accompanied%20by%20budgetary%20cuts%20in%20rural%20development%20schemes%2C%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Krishi%20Sinchai%20Yojana%2C%20cooperation%2C%20food%20storage%20and%20warehousing%2C%20plantations%2C%20crop%20husbandry%2C%20flood%20control%20and%20drainage%2C%20land%20reforms%2C%20fertilizer%20subsidy%2C%20food%20subsidy%2C%20dairy%20development%2C%20soil%20and%20water%20conservation%2C%20irrigation%2C%20nutrition%2C%20rural%20roads%2C%20housing%2C%20education%20and%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20quite%20clear%20from%20these%20macro-fiscal%20numbers%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20fiscal%20priority%20towards%20farmers%20and%20rural%20India%2C%20how%20the%20Modi%20Government%20is%20promoting%20the%20private%20sector%20in%20its%20fiscal%20policy%20and%20is%20still%20ready%20to%20embrace%20a%20strategy%20that%20promotes%20corporatisation%20of%20farming%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20own%20welfare%20and%20economic%20wellbeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Dean%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Interdisciplinarity%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%20has%20Visiting%20positions%20at%20University%20of%20London%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University%20(to%20name%20a%20few).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708155201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27210340%2FEffect.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fon-msp-modi-government-must-display-maturity-and-give-farmers-their-due%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20discussion%20must%20move%20from%20being%20an%20ego%20tussle%20between%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20farmers%2C%20into%20a%20clear%20fiscal%20priority%20for%20the%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fon-msp-modi-government-must-display-maturity-and-give-farmers-their-due%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Total%20devastation'%3A%20Home%20explodes%20with%20firefighters%20inside%2C%20killing%20one%20and%20injuring%20nine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708154880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-explosion-house-virginia_6458578.jpg%3F20240217092343%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fvirginia-home-explosion-firefighter-killed-and-11-people-injured-including-two-civilians-13073565%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20firefighter%20has%20been%20killed%20and%20nine%20others%20were%20injured%20after%20an%20explosion%20in%20a%20house%20where%20they%20were%20investigating%20a%20gas%20leak%2C%20US%20officials%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41