nt%2Fbranding-over-welfare-union-withholds-funds-from-bengal-for-not-displaying-pm-photo-at-ration-shops%5C%22%3Ehas%20withheld%20funds%20from%20West%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20refusing%20to%20print%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20photographs%20on%20bags%20used%20to%20distribute%20ration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20news%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20COVID-19%20vaccination%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-only-nation-to-use-covid-vaccination-certificate-to-push-cult-of-leader-ruling-party%5C%22%3Ecertificates%20had%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20photo%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20it%20had%20caused%20global%20flutter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708151325000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17115300%2F7637937542_b870fe2c5e_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpre-election-pm-modi-logos-on-pds-grain-bags-to-cost-crores-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20directive%20from%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20to%20float%20new%20tenders%20for%20such%20bags%20comes%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20held%20by%20May%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpre-election-pm-modi-logos-on-pds-grain-bags-to-cost-crores-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MGNREGA%20Led%20to%20Decline%20in%20Gender%20Wage%20Gap%2C%20Increased%20Compliance%20with%20Minimum%20Wage%20Norms%3A%20ILO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11115728%2Fmnrega-work.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20implementation%20and%20expansion%20of%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(MGNREGA)%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20decline%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%20besides%20increasing%20compliance%20with%20minimum%20wage%20regulations%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%20(ILO)%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20are%20from%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20latest%20working%20paper%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fglobal%2Fpublications%2Fworking-papers%2FWCMS_911918%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmployment%20and%20wage%20disparities%20between%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20has%20also%20decreased%20due%20to%20the%20employment%20guarantee%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20NREGS%20was%20introduced%20and%20expanded%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20compliance%20with%20minimum%20wage%20regulations%20increased%2C%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20decreased%20and%2C%20similarly%2C%20the%20gender%20wage%20gaps%20in%20rural%20areas%20declined.%20Alongside%20other%20factors%2C%20the%20NREGS%20programme%20seems%20to%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20these%20positive%20trends%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fmgnrega-scheme-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-in-rural-india-ilo-124021600730_1.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20the%20scheme%20has%20been%20successful%20in%20transforming%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20rural%20populace%2C%20the%20degree%20of%20impact%20varied%20across%20the%20nation%20depending%20on%20its%20implementation%20at%20the%20field%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20was%20passed%20in%202005%2C%20and%20the%20demand-driven%20scheme%20guarantees%20100%20days%20of%20unskilled%20work%20per%20year%20for%20every%20rural%20household%20that%20wants%20it.%20Since%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%20assumed%20power%20in%202014%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnrega-budget-allocation-2023-24%5C%22%3Ebudgetary%20allocations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20scheme%20have%20been%20reduced%20drastically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20famously%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmnrega-monument-to-failure-of-congress-govts-modi%2Farticle10701735.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3Ecalled%20MGNREGA%20a%20%E2%80%9Cliving%20monument%20of%20Congress%20government%E2%80%99s%20failure%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20speech%20in%20parliament%2C%20he%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20so%20many%20years%20in%20power%2C%20all%20you%20were%20able%20to%20deliver%20is%20for%20a%20poor%20man%20to%20dig%20ditches%20a%20few%20days%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ILO%20working%20paper%20also%20points%20to%20negative%20trends%20in%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20rural%20Indian%20wages%20in%20recent%20years.%20%E2%80%9CDrawing%20on%20inflation%20data%2C%20together%20with%20the%20rural%20monthly%20wage%20index%20published%20by%20the%20Indian%20Labour%20Bureau%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20has%20observed%20negative%20trends%20in%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20rural%20Indian%20wages%20in%20recent%20years.%20Thus%2C%20in%20its%20Economic%20Survey%202022-23%2C%20the%20Ministry%20highlighted%20a%20negative%20growth%20in%20real%20rural%20wages%20(that%20is%2C%20rural%20wages%20adjusted%20for%20inflation)%20due%20to%20elevated%20inflation%20between%20April%20and%20November%202022%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20study%20uses%20household%20survey%20data%20from%2058%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20to%20compare%20the%20labour%20market%20outcomes%20of%20rural%20and%20urban%20workers%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20specific%20socio-demographic%20characteristics%20of%20rural%20populations.%20It%20also%20provides%20an%20overview%20of%20the%20legal%20frameworks%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20address%20rural-urban%20employment%20and%20wage%20disparities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStatistical%20evidence%20from%2058%20countries%20shows%20that%20although%20people%20in%20rural%20areas%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20employment%20than%20those%20in%20urban%20ones%2C%20they%20also%20tend%20to%20have%20jobs%20that%20can%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20experiencing%20inadequate%20labour%20protection%20as%20well%20as%20low%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20particular%2C%20rural%20workers%20are%20paid%2C%20on%20average%2C%2024%25%20less%20than%20their%20urban%20counterparts%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%2C%20and%20only%20half%20of%20this%20gap%20can%20be%20explained%20by%20rural-urban%20discrepancies%20in%20education%2C%20job%20experience%20and%20occupational%20category.%20Developing%20countries%20exhibit%20a%20relatively%20wider%20gap%2C%20with%20the%20unexplained%20part%20also%20being%20larger.%20Furthermore%2C%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20certain%20groups%20of%20rural%20workers%20are%20at%20greater%20disadvantage%2C%20such%20as%20women%2C%20who%2C%20on%20average%2C%20appear%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20men%20in%20rural%20areas.%20However%2C%20institutional%20and%20regulatory%20frameworks%2C%20notably%20those%20that%20set%20minimum%20wages%20or%20seek%20to%20promote%20equal%20opportunities%2C%20can%20help%20to%20reduce%20labour%20market-related%20inequalities%20across%20the%20rural-urban%20divide%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708150169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11115728%2Fmnrega-work.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmgnrega-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-increased-compliance-with-minimum-wage-norms-ilo%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20working%20paper%20by%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%20has%20also%20found%20that%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20has%20also%20decreased%20due%20to%20the%20employment%20guarantee%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmgnrega-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-increased-compliance-with-minimum-wage-norms-ilo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alexei%20Navalny's%20Death%20Spells%20the%20End%20of%20Politics%20in%20Russia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17104400%2FScreenshot-2024-02-17-at-10.42.2.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EReports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F16%2Frussian-activist-and-putin-critic-alexei-navalny-dies-in-prison%5C%22%3Eof%20the%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20most%20famous%20opposition%20leader%2C%20Alexei%20Navalny%2C%20in%20an%20Arctic%20prison%20camp%20are%20shocking%2C%20but%20not%20entirely%20unexpected.%20It%20draws%20a%20line%20under%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20political%20development%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20by%20highlighting%20that%20a%20challenge%20from%20within%20is%20no%20longer%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20was%20the%20last%20public%20politician%20to%20pose%20a%20real%20challenge%20to%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20but%20his%20attempt%20to%20overthrow%20the%20regime%20failed%20long%20before%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20his%20untimely%20death%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20unrealistic%20calculations%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20his%20return%20to%20Russia%20in%202021%20led%20to%20the%20dismantling%20of%20the%20remnants%20of%20any%20organised%20opposition%20that%20was%20not%20sanctioned%20%E2%80%93%20and%20controlled%20%E2%80%93%20by%20the%20Russian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20ended%20up%20in%20prison%2C%20his%20supporters%20arrested%20or%20fled%20abroad.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20when%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20came%2C%20there%20were%20very%20few%20street%20protests%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActive%20in%20Russian%20politics%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2FwireStory%2Fprotests-poisoning-prison-life-russian-opposition-leader-alexei-107288919%23%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20main%20focus%20was%20identifying%20and%20rooting%20out%20state%20corruption%2C%20an%20issue%20with%20almost%20limitless%20material%20in%20modern%20Russia.%20He%20embraced%20new%20methods%20of%20bringing%20his%20investigations%20to%20as%20wide%20an%20audience%20as%20he%20could%2C%20notably%20the%20internet%2C%20particularly%20via%20his%20YouTube%20channel.%20Some%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1202972%2Fmost-popular-videos-by-alexei-navalny%2F%5C%22%3Emost%20popular%20clips%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20corruption%20investigations%20and%20blogging%20were%20not%20enough%20to%20really%20challenge%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20status%20quo%20in%20Russian%20politics.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20Navalny%20increasingly%20turned%20to%20the%20direct%20action%20of%20mass%20street%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20big%20break%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2011%2Fdec%2F10%2Frussia-protests-election-vladimir-putin%5C%22%3Ecame%20in%202011%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20allegations%20of%20widespread%20fraud%20in%20the%20December%202011%20Duma%20elections%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20announcement%20of%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20the%20presidency%20the%20previous%20September%2C%20brought%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20protesters%20on%20to%20the%20streets%20of%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20protests%20were%20not%20organised%20by%20Navalny%2C%20his%20charisma%20and%20more%20radical%20rhetoric%20made%20him%20the%20most%20prominent%20face%20of%20the%20protests%2C%20overshadowing%20more%20established%20opposition%20leaders%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2015%2Fmar%2F01%2Fboris-nemtsov%5C%22%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20mass%20protests%20of%202011-12%20failed%20to%20prevent%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20re-election%20in%20March%202012%2C%20and%20eventually%20fizzled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20protests%20prompted%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20change%20tack%20and%20experiment%20with%20allowing%20the%20opposition%20to%20stand%20in%20elections.%20Navalny%20was%20the%20main%20beneficiary%2C%20being%20registered%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2013%2Fsep%2F09%2Falexei-navalny-recount-moscow-election%5C%22%3EMoscow%20mayoral%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202013.%20This%20was%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20only%20real%20chance%20of%20winning%20power%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20tightly%20controlled%20electoral%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20campaigned%20enthusiastically%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2013%2Fsep%2F09%2Falexei-navalny-recount-moscow-election%5C%22%3Ewon%20a%20respectable%2027%25%20of%20the%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20also%20showed%20the%20limits%20of%20his%20appeal.%20Moscow%20was%20at%20the%20time%20one%20of%20the%20most%20opposition-leaning%20cities%20in%20Russia%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20regions%20where%20Putin%20got%20less%20than%2050%25%20in%20the%202012%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20opposition%20could%20really%20challenge%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20it%20was%20in%20Moscow.%20But%20turnout%20was%20extremely%20low%20at%2032%25%2C%20and%20the%20incumbent%20mayor%2C%20Sergey%20Sobyanin%2C%20won%20the%2051%25%20he%20needed%20to%20avoid%20a%20run-off%20with%20Navalny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20indicative%20of%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20problem%3A%20reliance%20on%20restriction%20to%20a%20committed%20core%20of%20supporters%20whose%20passion%20for%20change%20didn%E2%80%99t%20spill%20over%20into%20the%20general%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELast%20roll%20of%20the%20dice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElections%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20Russia%20are%20a%20foregone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fputin-is-sure-to-win-so-whats-the-point-of-elections-in-russia-93170%5C%22%3Econclusion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they%20are%20also%20a%20potential%20vulnerability%20for%20the%20Kremlin.%20There%20is%20a%20fine%20balance%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20to%20strike%20between%20control%20of%20elections%20and%20their%20legitimacy.%20Too%20much%20control%2C%20or%20outright%20fraud%2C%20and%20the%20legitimising%20value%20of%20the%20elections%20is%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20lead%20to%20potentially%20destabilising%20results%2C%20as%20the%20mass%20protests%20in%20Moscow%20in%202011%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2021%2F01%2F13%2Fbelarus-unprecedented-crackdown%5C%22%3Eprotests%20in%20Belarus%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%2C%20and%20as%20happened%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2004%2Fnov%2F26%2Fukraine.usa%5C%22%3E2004%20Ukrainian%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fukrainealert%2Fhow-ukraines-orange-revolution-shaped-twenty-first-century-geopolitics%2F%5C%22%3Efirst%20Orange%20Revolution%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20understood%20this%20well%2C%20and%20made%20participation%20in%20the%202018%20presidential%20election%20his%20main%20goal.%20His%20strategy%20was%20to%20cause%20enough%20trouble%20for%20the%20authorities%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20vote%2C%20particularly%20through%20various%20street%20demonstrations%2C%20to%20force%20the%20authorities%20to%20allow%20him%20to%20stand%20as%20an%20official%20candidate%20in%20these%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20he%20set%20up%20a%20regional%20network%20of%20Navalny%20HQs%20that%20ran%20in%20parallel%20with%20his%20main%20anti-corruption%20organisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Frussia-navalny-corruption-foundation%2F31938527.html%5C%22%3EFBK%20(the%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20gave%20Navalny%20a%20potential%20nationwide%20reach%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20old%20Moscow-centred%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20didn%E2%80%99t%20produce%20the%20desired%20result%20of%20getting%20Navalny%20on%20to%20the%20ballot.%20But%20it%20seemed%20to%20rattle%20the%20authorities%20enough%20to%20want%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CNavalny%20problem%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoison%20and%20imprisonment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20Navalny%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-suspected-poisoning-why-opposition-figure-stands-out-in-russian-politics-144836%5C%22%3Efell%20ill%20on%20a%20flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20according%20to%20the%20German%20doctors%20who%20treated%20him%2C%20escaped%20near-certain%20death%20from%20a%20Novichok%20weapons-grade%20chemical%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20returned%20from%20Germany%20in%20January%202021%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-novichok-didnt-stop-russian-opposition-leader-but-a-prison-sentence-might-153480%5C%22%3Eimmediately%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20landing%20in%20Moscow.%20The%20mass%20protests%20that%20followed%20were%20unusual%20for%20their%20regional%20scale%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20really%20challenge%20the%20Kremlin.%20Instead%2C%20the%20authorities%20banned%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20in%20Russia%20and%20either%20arrested%20or%20forced%20those%20who%20worked%20for%20them%20to%20flee%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%E2%80%99s%20fate%20became%20the%20main%20point%20of%20contention%20for%20Moscow%20in%20its%20dealings%20with%20western%20governments%20and%20media.%20Navalny%20was%20the%20obligatory%20subject%20of%20high-level%20contacts%20with%20the%20Russian%20authorities%2C%20with%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20adviser%20Jake%20Sullivan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-56794744%5C%22%3Ewarning%20that%20Russia%20would%20suffer%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20Navalny%20died%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20this%20paled%20into%20insignificance%20after%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%202022.%20Overnight%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20fate%20seemed%20diminished%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20war%20since%201945.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%E2%80%99s%20own%20agenda%20of%20generating%20enough%20domestic%20protest%20to%20topple%20the%20regime%20became%20obsolete%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2022%2F03%2Frussia-kremlins-ruthless-crackdown-stifles-independent-journalism-and-anti-war-movement%2F%5C%22%3Enew%20anti-opposition%20laws%20were%20enforced%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20most%20of%20his%20most%20ardent%20supporters%20fled%20the%20country.%20Navalny%20tried%20to%20stay%20relevant%20by%20promoting%20his%20views%20from%20prison%2C%20including%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F4fishgreenberg.medium.com%2Falexey-navalny-on-the-anniversary-of-the-russian-invasion-of-ukraine-2aa18f5602c4%5C%22%3Ecall%20to%20end%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20handing%20over%20all%20Ukrainian%20territory%2C%20including%20Crimea%2C%20and%20paying%20reparations%20to%20Ukraine.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20that%20he%20gained%20any%20supporters%20in%20Russia%2C%20but%20he%20certainly%20appealed%20to%20those%20in%20exile%20and%20to%20western%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20West%20and%20its%20allies%20imposing%20an%20unprecedented%20level%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20and%20providing%20Ukraine%20with%20the%20military%20support%20to%20defeat%20Putin%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20literally%20nothing%20else%20the%20west%20can%20do%20to%20punish%20Russia%20over%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20rest%20is%20dictatorship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny%20was%20clearly%20a%20very%20brave%20and%20charismatic%20politician%20who%20posed%20the%20most%20significant%20domestic%20challenge%20to%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20regime%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20He%20never%20really%20came%20close%20to%20toppling%20Putin%2C%20and%20perhaps%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-novichok-didnt-stop-russian-opposition-leader-but-a-prison-sentence-might-153480%5C%22%3Eoverestimated%20his%20level%20of%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20news%20of%20his%20untimely%20death%20in%20prison%2C%20the%20question%20remains%20whether%20he%20could%20have%20done%20more%20from%20exile%20in%20the%20west.%20He%20would%20have%20joined%20a%20long%20list%20of%20Russian%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20from%20former%20oligarch%20Mikhail%20Khodorkovsky%20to%20chess%20champion%20Garry%20Kasparov%2C%20who%20have%20virtually%20no%20influence%20on%20what%20happens%20in%20Russia.%20But%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20go%20down%20that%20road%2C%20and%20his%20belief%20in%20his%20own%20importance%2C%20is%20precisely%20what%20has%20made%20him%20stand%20out%20in%20Russian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20death%20draws%20a%20line%20under%20the%20era%20when%20politics%20was%20politics%20in%20Russia.%20Today%20there%20is%20only%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20own%20personal%20authoritarianism.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%